{{Politics of North Korea}}
'''Vice President of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea''' was a political position in [[North Korea]] established in 1972, and abolished after the death of [[Kim Il-sung]] during the reign of [[Kim Jong-il]].
In 1972 the Presidency was established, and Kim Il-sung was elected to the position by the [[Supreme People's Assembly]], the North Korean [[legislature]], on 28 December 1972. The Vice Presidents were also elected by the Assembly.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=D6mFCwAAQBAJ|title=Political Handbook of the World 1998|first1=Arthur S.|last1=Banks|first2=Alan J.|last2=Day|first3=Thomas C.|last3=Muller|first4=0|last4=0|date=1 February 2016|publisher=Springer|via=Google Books}}</ref>
